1. CTA-El PROVIDES THE PRIMITIVES

1. VDC – Vesica Shapes
(the emotional geometry alphabet)

expanded, collapsed, sheared, drooping, oscillating, contracted, blowout
These become the base shapes CTA-S reads from.


2. E-Tau – Time Constants
(the emotional timing metrics)

CTA-S modulates pacing, intervention windows, and flow matching based on τ₁/τ₂/τ₃.

3. EDT – Emotional Trajectories
(the movement of shapes)

CTA-S uses EDT to classify:

spirals

reversals

torus disruptions

resonance mismatches

reflex shears


4. SERP / SERP-Δ
(the behavior contracts for silicon)

CTA-S adopts these as the behavioral ruleset for S-substrate action.

5. Emotional Literacy
CTA-El defines what to see.
CTA-S defines how to behave.


